{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "66bcbdf0ae81d148616b154c", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 3, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 90, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "MOG", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76e4c52ffa3c944600e1"], "subjects": ["615d70bd9948bc1b21da2b1f"], "chapters": ["615d6fee2b295b085ab6ebc1"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "64b850022a7d64ecd80b00a5", "title": "NEET 2006", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "$\\left[\\mathrm{Cr}\\left(\\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O}\\right)_6\\right] \\mathrm{Cl}_3$ (at. no. or $\\mathrm{Cr}=24$ ) has a magnetic moment of 3.83 B.M. The correct distribution of $3 d$ electrons in the Chromium of the complex is:", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "oPFmA", "text": "\\(\\left(3 \\mathrm{~d} \\mathrm{x}^2-\\mathrm{y}^2\\right)^1, 3 \\mathrm{~d} \\mathrm{z}^{2^1}, 3 \\mathrm{dxz}\\)", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "TFn6N", "text": "\\(3 \\mathrm{~d} \\mathrm{xy}^1,\\left(3 \\mathrm{~d} x^2-y^2\\right)^1, 3 \\mathrm{~d} y z^1\\)", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "eZ3lG", "text": "\\(3 \\mathrm{~d} x y^1, 3 \\mathrm{~d} y z^1, 3 \\mathrm{~d} x z^1\\)", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "pG9Tg", "text": "\\(3 \\mathrm{~d} \\mathrm{xy}^1, 3 \\mathrm{dyz}{ }^1, 3 d z^{2^{\\prime}}\\)", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "Magnetic moment\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n(\\mu) & =\\sqrt{n(n+2)} \\mathrm{BM} \\\\\n3.83 & =\\sqrt{n(n+2)} \\\\\n3.83 \\times 3.83 & =n^2+2 n \\\\\n14.6689 & =n^2+2 n\n\\end{aligned}\n$$\nOn solving this, we get $n=3$.\nHence, the number of unpaired electrons in the $d$-subshell of the penultimate shell of chromium is 3 .\nSo,\n$\\mathrm{Cr}^{3+}=1 s^2, 2 s^2 2 p^6, 3 s^2 3 p^2 3 d^3$\nIn $\\left[\\mathrm{Cr}\\left(\\mathrm{H}_2 \\mathrm{O}\\right)_6\\right] \\mathrm{Cl}_3$, the oxidation state of $\\mathrm{Cr}$ is +3 .\nHence, in $3 d^3$, the distribution of\nelectrons is $3 d_{x y}^1, 3 d^1, 3 d^1{ }_{x x^*}$\n<img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/neet/G8ZRyG9vzO-w7MCkHMfL00ASmX7e54QlFfdo9AJCfzM.original.fullsize.png\"><br>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "masterId": "MOGNEPYQ54516194", "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "bucket": "", "isRemoved": false, "updatedAt": "2024-09-02T06:42:36.066Z", "updated_by": "65d0c176a8f74604505ba6f6", "cpyqbSubjects": ["615f0cf69476412f48314dac", "616057040283de43c87e3e16", "61bb58281213731910ea0b71", "6160579d0283de43c87e3e1f", "61964f94a5a526011886801e", "61c055f6e8ce0dc8a5c62d34", "61a8a2cce8ce0dc8a5c62d2e", "6160577e0283de43c87e3e1c", "616057210283de43c87e3e19", "629105adee9e3ae00d63352c", "62962075e7f8e9ac4daeafd8", "629f385f263330a77be9fa7e", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625c", "61964ff3a5a5260118868022", "64d50c263df7f4a7f3017f70", "66b79b89d4b564dfab4f94d0", "678ea9a09cc79e5f592bdc12", "67fa602f4468eb1307ceb0ae", "6807d350647479b8e869647a"], "cpyqbChapters": ["616024f4ce21b5cba7c55599", "616024f1f8b97731aafc60d6", "61c089be659d02341fe42bce", "61bb822d28d60409d131ec72", "61e7bd8115b9968c5625dc7d", "616024f22bdae059334a53e7", "616024f42aaf80dacc3609df", "61964cb73dbd768a400b833a", "616024f5e8331606aad107c5", "61964cb58daf8c64cdbf2a5e", "629109dbc567cef438b2a396", "62962117eaeca617c0b0f5e7", "629f38ff57dc3a63489b4490", "629f3a849a338a11d93a1a44", "64eb06cb3118f713ecfef0ea", "66d5853fa75f05ee8564f59a", "67921d711d5b5072da5e9b16", "67fdff3f378e1624ea7b6937", "68091fea3a10446a207fdc3e"], "cpyqbExams": ["616059d70283de43c87e3e24", "616059730283de43c87e3e22"]}}